# A try/catch that runs INSIDE a finally, and fully handles its own exception, must not steal the
# blame: the exception the finally is unwinding (line 5) is what escapes, so line 5 is what the
# diagnostic must name — not line 8, the inner throw that was already dealt with. (v1.15 A04-1)
var f = Function():
    try:
        throw "original-error"
    finally:
        try:
            throw "inner-handled"
        catch String as e:
            discard e

f()
